25/10/2009
ATHENS, Greece -- Three homemade bombs were placed in front of the offices of leading PASOK politicians in Thessaloniki on Friday (October 23rd). One bomb blew up in front of the private office of Deputy Civil Protection Minister Spyros Vougias but did not injure anyone. The other two bombs were found outside the offices of Justice Minister Harris Kastanidis and a PASOK lawmaker but did not blow up. (Reuters, AP - 23/10/09)
